# Smart Bookmark App - Setup Guide

## Prerequisites

This app uses Firebase for:
- **Authentication** (Google OAuth)
- **Realtime Database** (for storing and syncing bookmarks)

## Step-by-Step Setup

### 1. Create a Firebase Project

1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/)
2. Click "Add project" or "Create a project"
3. Enter a name (e.g., "smart-bookmark-app")
4. Disable Google Analytics (optional, for simpler setup)
5. Wait for project creation to complete

### 2. Enable Google Sign-In

1. In Firebase Console, go to **Authentication** (left sidebar)
2. Click **Sign-in method** tab
3. Click **Add new provider**
4. Select **Google**
5. Enable it (toggle to ON)
6. Select a support email (your email)
7. Click **Save**

### 3. Create a Web App

1. In Firebase Console, click the **</>** (Web) icon
2. Register app: enter name (e.g., "Smart Bookmark")
3. Check "Also set up Firebase Hosting" (optional)
4. Click **Register app**
5. Copy the `firebaseConfig` object shown

### 4. Update the Code

1. Open `index.html` in a code editor
2. Find the `firebaseConfig` object (around line 280)
3. Replace the placeholder values with your actual Firebase config:

```
javascript
const firebaseConfig = {
    apiKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
    authDomain: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID.firebaseapp.com",
    projectId: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
    storageBucket: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID.appspot.com",
    messagingSenderId: "YOUR_SENDER_ID",
    appId: "YOUR_APP_ID",
    databaseURL: "https://YOUR_PROJECT_ID-default-rtdb.firebaseio.com"
};
```

### 5. Test the App

1. Open `index.html` in a browser (or serve it locally)
2. Click "Sign in with Google"
3. You should see a Google popup to sign in
4. After signing in, you can add bookmarks

## Firebase Config Values Explained

| Value | Where to Find |
|-------|---------------|
| `apiKey` | Firebase Console > Project Settings > General > Your apps |
| `authDomain` | `{project-id}.firebaseapp.com` |
| `projectId` | Project ID from project settings |
| `storageBucket` | `{project-id}.appspot.com` |
| `messagingSenderId` | Project Settings > Cloud Messaging |
| `appId` | Project Settings > Your apps > App ID |
| `databaseURL` | `{project-id}-default-rtdb.firebaseio.com` |

## Important Notes

### Security Rules (Optional but Recommended)

In Firebase Console > Realtime Database > Rules, you can set:

```
json
{
  "rules": {
    "bookmarks": {
      "$uid": {
        ".read": "auth != null && auth.uid === $uid",
        ".write": "auth != null && auth.uid === $uid"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

This ensures users can only see their own bookmarks!

### Deployment

To deploy your app:

1. Install Firebase CLI: `npm install -g firebase-tools`
2. Login: `firebase login`
3. Initialize: `firebase init`
4. Deploy: `firebase deploy`

Or use Netlify, Vercel, or GitHub Pages (just upload the HTML file).

## Troubleshooting

### "Firebase not configured" error
- Make sure you've updated the `firebaseConfig` in the code
- Check that all values are filled in (no "YOUR_" placeholders)

### "Sign-in blocked" error
- Go to Firebase Console > Authentication > Sign-in method
- Make sure Google sign-in is enabled
- Check that your email is listed in the authorized domains

### Bookmarks not syncing
- Check the browser console (F12) for errors
- Make sure you're using the same Google account
- Check Firebase Realtime Database rules

## Features Included

✅ Google OAuth sign-in (no email/password)  
✅ Add bookmarks with URL and title  
✅ Private bookmarks (only visible to signed-in user)  
✅ Real-time sync across tabs and devices  
✅ Delete bookmarks  
✅ Dark theme with modern UI  
✅ Responsive design
